result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of State, Court ordered case dismissed.

Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner in court, in custody and appears pro se.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk     Defendant advised of right to counsel.  Court examined defendant as to his waiver of counsel.  Court finds defendant freely and voluntarily waives his right to counsel.

Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner not in court, defendant in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The defendant has pending felony matters.  Attorney Thomas Flanagan did not appear.  The clerk left voicemail message and text message for defense counsel.  Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 24.  Status conference scheduled for October 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed, Letter from Attorney Bihler.

Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner not in court, defendant in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defendant not produced. Defendant has a pending case in Felony court. This case is to follow felony case. Defense attorney on felony matter made aware of pending misdemeanor case.  Status conference scheduled for October 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Douglas Michael Bihler in court, defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner not in court, in custody.  Katherine Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defense counsel advised the Court that attorney Thomas Flanagan is representing the defendant in a pending felony matter.  Defense motion to withdraw as counsel is granted by the Court.  Court ordered case adjourned for status of counsel in Branch 24.  Clerk notified attorney Flanagan of the new court date.  Status conference scheduled for August 25, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Bihler contacted the court to reschedule the pretrial conference because he's on vacation through August 17, 2015.  Pretrial conference rescheduled to August 19, 2015 at 8:30 am in Branch 24.

Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner not in court, defendant in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case calendared for a pre-trial conference, however, the appointed attorney did not appear. Court ordered case adjourned for pretrial conference in Branch 24. Court to notify atty Bihler of new date.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 7, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION.
Court ordered defendant to be monitored by Drug Testing
Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.

Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner in court with attorney Anne A. Devitt.  Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner in custody.  
Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  

DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  
Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Ulandas Rezza Turner not in court.  Brandon A Wigley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued.  Court ordered any bail posted to be forfeited.  State's motion for Judgment of Bond Forfeiture 30 days after notification from the Clerk of Circuit Court's Office is granted by the Court.  Court makes finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, recompense is not an issue.
SUMMONS MAILED. DEFENDANT ORDERED INTO ROOM 221 SAFETY BUILDING ON 5/13/15 @ 1:30 pm
